SIMPLE: singleness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Singleness
<hw>Sin"gle*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being single, or separate from all others; the opposite of
doubleness, complication, or multiplicity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Freedom from duplicity, or secondary and selfish
ends; purity of mind or purpose; simplicity; sincerity; <as>as,
<ex>singleness</ex> of purpose; <ex>singleness</ex> of
heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>singles</ent>⟦br⟧
